# OpenAPI Documentation

## Keep OpenAPI Up to Date

When adding or modifying REST endpoints in the NOCS API:

1. **Add `@Operation`** to every controller method with `summary` and `description`
2. **Add `@ApiResponse`** for each HTTP status (200, 201, 204, 400, 404, etc.)
3. **Add `@Tag`** to controller classes for grouping in Swagger UI
4. **Add `@Schema`** to request/response DTOs and records for field descriptions and required flags

## Annotations Reference

```java
@Tag(name = "ResourceName", description = "Brief description")
@Operation(summary = "Short summary", description = "Detailed description")
@ApiResponse(responseCode = "200", description = "Success")
@Schema(description = "Field description", requiredMode = Schema.RequiredMode.REQUIRED)
```

## Endpoints

- **OpenAPI spec (JSON)**: `GET /api/v1/v3/api-docs`
- **Swagger UI**: `GET /api/v1/swagger-ui.html`

## Checklist

Before completing API changes:
- [ ] New endpoints have @Operation and @ApiResponse
- [ ] New DTOs/records have @Schema on fields
- [ ] Run app and verify Swagger UI reflects changes at `/api/v1/swagger-ui.html`
